Pre-Game Insights: Spencer Arrighetti has been great this month with a 2.55 ERA and a.193 batting average against him.
Taijuan Walker has really struggled this season, especially lately, with a 9.26 ERA and allowing 16 hits in 11.2 innings.
The Astros are one of the top offenses in the MLB and should be able to get to Walker in this game.
Arrighetti has a 10.4 percent walk rate, which means the Phillies can expect a few walks.
Philadelphia is playing some good baseball right now and has won a series against the Kansas City Royals.
The Phillies are a much better team at home this season, as they are almost 20 games over.500 at Citizens Bank Ballpark.
